Prerequisite:
	1. Attend Agile session from youtube/ITMS
	2. SDLC.- TutorialsPoint.com
	3. Devops Fundamentals/Foundation: ITMS., FutureSkills.(20 Qurated skills of Devops)



CI/CD--> 

	• CI: Dev, Coding, Testing and Notification

	• Dev--> Committed to SCM --> CI

	• Advantages of CI:
		a. Reduced integration risk
		b. Higher code quality
		c. Appropriate version control
		d. Reduced conflicts between team members
		e. Less time for deployment.
		f. Transparent to the client and having increased confidence.

	• Tools used in Devops:
		○ Build tools- Shell, powershell, batch, maven, Ant, MS-Build, PyBuilder
		○ Test Tools- MS-Test, Nunit, Junit, 
		○ SCM-SVN, Git, Github, Gitlab, bitbucket
		○ Deployment- Cloud(AWS, GCP, Azure), Docker, AppServer- Tomcat, Jboss, Glassfish, Weblogic, WebSphere, 
		○ Notification- e-Mail 
		○ Monitoring- Jenkins, Blue Ocean, Nagios, 
	• Environments to Practice Jenkins
		○ Raise request for TopGear VDI- DevOps-OS, DevOps-CITI
		○ Get a cloud access- Azure, AWS, GCP- Create a VM- Windows, Linux- Install Jenkins
		○ Create your own VM
How to get the jenkins credential:
	While Installalling jenkins keep watching the monitor, it will ask to copy the path of initial encrypted pwd.
